=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Looking at the mapped reaction, I need to identify the mechanistic class and reaction center.

**Analysis:**
- Reactant 1 is an enolate ester (C:11=C:10 with O⁻:12)
- Reactant 2 is benzofuroxan (electron-deficient N-oxide heterocycle)
- In the product, C:10 (enolate carbon) forms a new bond to C:20 (on the benzofuroxan ring), the C:11=C:10 double bond becomes single, and C:11=O:12 becomes an ester carbonyl
- The enolate nucleophile adds to the electrophilic position of the benzofuroxan aromatic ring, breaking aromaticity

**Mechanistic class:** Nucleophilic addition of a stabilized carbanion (enolate) to an electron-deficient heteroaromatic ring — a **nucleophilic aromatic addition** (not substitution, since no leaving group departs).

**Reaction center:** C:10–C:20 bond formation; C:11=C:10 π-bond cleavage; C:11–O:12 rehybridization (enolate → carbonyl).

nucleophilic_aromatic_addition; reaction_center: C10-C20 bond formation, C11=C10→C11-C10, C11-O12 enolate→carbonyl

